{
  "texts": [
    "Panel A findings for Python versus R. In our function analysis, for the initial GitHub Copilot release, commits with new function definitions increase by 0.593 per quarter while commits without new function definitions increase by 4.959 per quarter-a difference of 4.366 commits.",
    "Following the model upgrade, we observe additional increases of 0.345 for function-adding commits and 1.762 for non-function-adding commits.",
    "This suggests that the model improvement enhances both types of contributions, but maintains the substantial gap between them, with non-function-adding commits seeing a more substantial absolute boost from the enhanced contextual understanding capabilities.",
    "In our LLM categorization analysis, for the initial GitHub Copilot release, code development commits increase by 1.299 per quarter while maintenance commits increase by 1.730 per quarter-a difference of 0.431 commits.",
    "Following the model upgrade, we observe insignificant increase 0.288 for code development and a statistically significant increase for maintenance."
  ]
}